This paper discusses the phenomenon of adversarial examples in deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the mathematical analysis of the phenomenon and proposes a new perspective, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-categories. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CR.
